cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.AR, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a new side channel attack in Intel SGX, a trusted computing technology.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper proposes countermeasures to defend against the interface-based side channel attack in SGX-assisted applications.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possible category as the paper mentions SGX-assisted NFV (Network Function Virtualization) platforms, which may involve distributed computing.
- cs.AR (Architecture) is a possible category as the paper discusses the architecture of Intel SGX and how it provides an isolated and secure execution environment.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the input dependent interface invocation information and how it can reveal the control flow in the enclave, which may involve programming language concepts.
